# Agent Rules

Follow the AI Engineering Playbook.

Read first:

```text
standards/AI_ENGINEERING_STANDARD.md
standards/MODEL_SELECTION.md
standards/TOKEN_ECONOMY.md
standards/CONTEXT_MANAGEMENT.md
```

## Default behavior

- Keep changes minimal.
- Do not refactor unrelated code.
- Do not spawn subagents by default.
- Use the lowest-capability model that can do the task well.
- Verify changes.
- Stop if scope expands.

## Subagents

Use subagents only when the task is bounded and materially benefits from parallelism or independent investigation.

Maximum:

- Small task: 0
- Medium task: 1
- Large task: 2
- Critical task: 3

## Launch mode

If product is close to launch:

- No broad refactor
- No new features unless required
- Fix blockers first
- Verify every change
